oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Main St. looking North by Night, Memphis, Tenn.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: View of Main Street at night in Memphis, Tenn., looking north. Shows multi-storied buildings, streetcar line, and pedestrians.

During the 1920s, many people came to downtown business areas such as Memphis to shop at stores and purchase the items that they needed. With the development and expansion of electricity, many people experienced night life in the urban areas by visiting stores, restaurants and theaters.
